20 WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Inc., is a collegiate Greek-letter
21 fraternity founded on January 5, 1911, at Indiana University in Bloomington;
22 and
23
24 WHEREAS, Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Inc., has over one hundred fifty
25 thousand (150,000) members in seven hundred (700) undergraduate and alumni
26 chapters in every state of the United States and around the world; and
27
28 WHEREAS, the members of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, Inc., are risk
29 takers, trailblazers, and changemakers with a passion for achievement in
30 every field of human endeavor, uplifting their communities, and developing
31 the current and next generation of leaders; and
32
33 WHEREAS, at the time of the founding of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity,
34 Inc., in Bloomington, Indiana, Indiana was a stronghold for the Ku Klux Klan,
35 but despite the hostility toward Blacks in Indiana, some Black students
36 sought a college education at Indiana University as it was a tuition-free
